r ses qualit√©s p√©dagogiques. Beaucoup d‚Äôadolescents peuvent en effet s‚Äôidentifier √† Charlie. M√©lanie Laurent elle-m√™me a confess√© avoir fait l‚Äôexp√©rience du harc√®lement scolaire.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Thriller/suspens :</strong></h3>\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>¬†La prochaine fois je viserai le c≈ìur (next time I‚Äôll aim for the heart)</strong> </span></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"%20https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8_fYnFVmeUw \" target=\"_blank\">Trailer</a>\r\nThis movie is definitely only for an adult audience. There aren‚Äôt any gory scenes as violence is suggested rather than explicitely shown but still the whole atmosphere is disturbing and scary !</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This thriller, which some reviewers compared to Fincher‚Äôs <em>Zodiac</em> is adapted from the novel \'Un assassin au-dessus de tout soup√ßon\' which was inspired by macabre events that occured in France in 1978 and 1979. A killer who worked as a gendarme (rural police officer) ended up investigating his own murders.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Like in the famous Tv show<em> Dexter</em>, we‚Äôre made to see the action throught the criminal‚Äôs perspective and follow him as he goes everytime a little further in his mad frenzy¬† while trying to maintain the righteous image of the perfect cop. The comparison stops there as the audience is given no justification for Frank‚Äôs terrible acts, no reason to sympathize or understand him. The man is just crazy and can‚Äôt control himself. That‚Äôs what is the most stricking in that movie : its raw and uncompromising aspect.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can find the DVD (I\'m not sure it has English subtitles though) <a href=\"http://www.amazon.fr/gp/product/B00R1UV7Z4/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1642&amp;creative=6746&amp;creativeASIN=B00R1UV7Z4&