n prison ¬ª ( a soul in jail). I haven‚Äôt found any translated version of that book but the original one is available for free (and legally) on the <a href=\"https://archive.org/details/UneAmeEnPrisonArnould1904%20\" target=\"_blank\">Internet archive website </a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The movie will be out on DVD on march 18th in France so it should become available abroad in the following weeks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Ce film est bas√© sur une histoire vraie. Il raconte comment, √† la fin du 19√®me si√®cle, Marie Heurtin, une jeune femme aveugle et sourde apprit la langue des signes gr√¢ce √† l‚Äôincroyable s≈ìur Marguerite. Tr√®s touchant, ce film est de ceux qui font √† la fois sourire et pleurer.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Les parents de Marie Heurtin refus√®rent d‚Äôenvoyer leur fille √† l‚Äôasile (la seule option offerte par l‚Äô√©tat √† l‚Äô√©poque). La jeune fille grandit comme ¬´ un animal sauvage ¬ª et se comportait parfois de fa√ßon violente.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Lorsque son p√®re l‚Äôemm√®ne √† l‚Äôinstitut Larnay, √©tablissement qui s‚Äôoccupe d‚Äôenfants sourds, on la classe dans les cas d√©sesp√©r√©s et elle serait renvoy√©e chez elle sans l‚Äôinsistance de s≈ìur Marguerite pour la prendre. Cette nonne d√©vou√©e va l‚Äôapprivoiser gr√¢ce √† son amour et sa patience puis lui apprendre √† communiquer.</em>\r\n<em> Ces √©v√©nements se d√©roulent dans la campagne du sud-ouest de la France et l‚Äôambiance g√©n√©rale donne un aper√ßu de ce √† quoi ressemblait la France rurale d‚Äôil y a 130 ans.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>L‚Äôhistoire de Marie devint c√©l√®bre en France en 1910 lorsque Louis Arnould √©crivit dessus dans un essai intitul√©¬´ Une √¢me en prison ¬ª. Il est disponible gratuitement (et l√©galement) <a href=\"https://archive.org/details/UneAmeEnPrisonArnould1904\" target=\"_blank\">ici</a>.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">¬†Hippocrate</span></strong></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Lc61Di-g-E4%20\" target=\"_blank\">Trailer¬† </a>\r\nIt‚Äôs a bit tricky to define that movie as it contains both elements of comedy and film noir. It explores the world of hospital and doctor‚Äôs daily dilemnas through the eyes of a rookie called Benjamin. For his first internship this idealist will have to work in the same hospital as his father and go through a rather tough initiation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many dysfunctionnal aspects of French hospitals are exposed such as futile medical care, the omnipresence of paperwork or how profit can sometimes come before patients‚Äôwell-being‚Ä¶ Prepare for some harsh criticism and cynism as in this film, doctors are not heroes or geniuses like in Doctor house but average joes and janes who have to deal with exhausting schedules and constant pressure.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This movie was part of Cannes Festival‚Äôs selection for 2014 and was nominated for best film at the C√©sars.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can watch this movie with English subtitles on some itunes store (it‚Äôs not available in every country) or buy the DVD in French with French subtitles <a href=\"%20http://www.amazon.fr/Hippocrate-Thomas-Lilty/dp/B00N43LSRE\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Il est assez difficile de d√©finir ce film puisqu‚Äôil contient √† la fois des √©l√©ments comiques et d‚Äôautres qui le rapprochent du film noir. Il explore le monde hospitalier et les dilemmes quotidiens des m√©decins √† travers les yeux de Benjamin, une jeune recrue. Pour son premier internat, cet id√©aliste va devoir travailler dans le m√™me h√¥pital que son p√®re et en passer par une initiation assez dure. De nombreux dysfonctionnements du syst√®me hospitalier fran√ßais sont expos√©s, tels que l‚Äôacharnement th√©rapeutique, l‚Äôomnipr√©sence de la paperasse administrative ou encore la fa√ßon dont les b√©n√©fices passent parfois avant le bien-√™tre des patients‚Ä¶Pr√©parez-vous √† de vives critiques et du cynisme car dans ce film, les m√©decins ne sont pas des h√©ros ou des g√©nies √† la fa√ßon d‚Äôun Docteur House, mais des monsieur et madame tout le monde qui doivent s‚Äôaccommoder d‚Äôhoraires √©puisants et d‚Äôune pression constante.</em>\r\n<em>Ce film a fait partie de la s√©lection 2014 du festival de Cannes et a √©t√© nomin√© dans la cat√©gorie meilleur film lors des C√©sars.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Respire/breath\r\n</strong></span></h5>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/respire_cadre.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-424\" src=\"http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/respire_cadre-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"respire_cadre\" width=\"220\" height=\"220\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VXncAEif-zY\" target=\"_blank\">Trailer</a>\r\nRespire deals with friendship and obsession. Charlie, a shy and introvert 17 years old is immediately fascinated by the new girl in school, the confident and charismatic Sarah. Soon she‚Äôs caught in the charmer‚Äôs web and turns her back to her best friend. Slowly the fusional relationship turns into a very toxic one. Sarah happens to be rather cruel and manipulative.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Respire is M√©lanie Laurent‚Äôs second movie as a director but she‚Äôs better know for her very international acting carreer : you might have seen her in Inglorious basterds, the enemy, Now you see me or Beginners. This extremely realistic movie has been shown in several French high-schools and has some pedagogical quality. Many teenagers can indeed identify with Charlie. M√©lanie Laurent herself has confessed that she has experience being bullied at school.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Soon to be released on DVD !</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Respire traite d‚Äôamiti√© et d‚Äôobsession. Charlie, une ado de 17 ans timide et introvertie, est imm√©diatement fascin√©e par la nouvelle venue au lyc√©e, la charismatique et s√ªre d‚Äôelle Sarah. Elle se retrouve rapidement prise dans les filets de cette s√©ductrice et tourne le dos √† sa meilleure amie. Lentement, l‚Äôamiti√© fusionnelle se transforme en relation toxique. Sarah est en fait de nature plut√¥t cruelle et manipulatrice. Respire est le deuxi√®me film de M√©lanie Laurent en tant que r√©alisatrice mais elle est plus connue pour sa tr√®s internationale carri√®re d‚Äôactrice : vous l‚Äôavez peut-√™tre vue dans Inglorious Basterds, the enemy, Now you see me ou Beginners. Ce film tr√®s r√©aliste a √©t√© projet√© dans plusieurs lyc√©es fran√ßais pour ses qualit√©s p√©dagogiques. Beaucoup d‚Äôadolescents peuvent en effet s‚Äôidentifier √† Charlie. M√©lanie Laurent elle-m√™me a confess√© avoir fait l‚Äôexp√©rience du harc√®lement scolaire.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Thriller/suspens :</strong></h3>\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>¬†La prochaine fois je viserai le c≈ìur (next time I‚Äôll aim for the heart)</strong> </span></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"%20https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8_fYnFVmeUw \" target=\"_blank\">Trailer</a>\r\nThis movie is definitely only for an adult audience. There aren‚Äôt any gory scenes as violence is suggested rather than explicitely shown but still the whole atmosphere is disturbing and scary !</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This thriller, which some reviewers compared to Fincher‚Äôs <em>Zodiac</em> is adapted from the novel \'Un assassin au-dessus de tout soup√ßon\' which was inspired by macabre events that occured in France in 1978 and 1979. A killer who worked as a gendarme (rural police officer) ended up investigating his own murders.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Like in the famous Tv show<em> Dexter</em>, we‚Äôre made to see the action throught the criminal‚Äôs perspective and follow him as he goes everytime a little further in his mad frenzy¬† while trying to maintain the righteous image of the perfect cop. The comparison stops there as the audience is given no justification for Frank‚Äôs terrible acts, no reason to sympathize or understand him. The man is just crazy and can‚Äôt control himself. That‚Äôs what is the most stricking in that movie : its raw and uncompromising aspect.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The DVD will be available in the very beginning of april. You can already preorder it <a href=\"http://www.amazon.co.uk/Next-Time-Ill-Aim-Heart/dp/B00TSEW8F4%3FSubscriptionId%3DAKIAIPZZSXFQRG4HNMCA%26tag%3Dvirginmedia-21%26linkCode%3Dxm2%26camp%3D2025%26creative%3D165953%26creativeASIN%3DB00TSEW8F4\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Ce films est d√©finitivement reserv√© √† un public adulte. Il n\'y a pas de sc√©nes gores puisque la violence est sugg√©r√©e plut√¥t qu\'explicit√©e, cependant l\'atmosph√®re est d√©rangeante et inqui√©tante. Ce thriller, que certains critiques ont compar√© √† Zodiac de David Fincher, est une adaptation du roman Un assassin au-dessus de tout soup√ßon, lui m√™me inspir√© d‚Äô√©v√©nements macabres qui eurent lieu en France entre 1978 et 1979. Un tueur faisant partie de la gendarmerie se retrouva √† enqu√™ter sur ses propres meurtres.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Comme dans la c√©l√®bre s√©rie Dexter, nous assistons √† l\'action depuis la perspective du criminel et nous le suivons alors qu\'il va √† chaque fois un peu plus loin dans sa folie meurtri√®re tout en cherchant √† maintenir son image vertueuse de flic parfait. La comparaison s\'arr√™te l√† puisque le spectateur ne se voit donner aucune justification pour les actes terribles commis par Franck, aucune raison de compatir ou de le comprendre. Cet homme est juste fou et ne peut se retenir. C\'est ce qui est le plus frappant dans ce film:¬† son aspect cru et sans compromis.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','2014 French movies you should watch (part 2) / Films fran√ßais sortis en 2014 que vous devriez regarder (2√®me partie)','','inherit','open','open','','414-revision-v1','','','2015-03-18 01:25:19','2015-03-18 00:25:19','',414,'http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/blog/2015/03/18/414-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(430,1,'2015-03-19 16:43:07','2015-03-19 15:43:07','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bells-157961_1280.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-thumbnail wp-image-433\" src=\"http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/bells-157961_1280-150x150.png\" alt=\"bells-157961_1280\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n\r\nEven though less and less French people celebrate Easter in a religious way, it is still one of the most popular holiday in France.\r\n\r\nHere is a short article on what you should know about it :\r\n<h5><strong>What :</strong></h5>\r\nEaster is called ¬´ P√¢ques ¬ª in French.\r\n\r\nThis word can be a bit confusing for French learners as it is a plural noun (hence the ‚Äìs ending) but it is used without any plural article. For example we say \"je vais f√™ter P√¢ques \"(I‚Äôm going to celebrate P√¢ques) and not \"je vais f√™ter<strong> les</strong> P√¢ques\".\r\n\r\nEaster day is called ¬´ le jour de P√¢ques ¬ª.\r\n\r\nMaundy Thursday is called ¬´ jeudi saint ¬ª (Holy Thursday)\r\n\r\nWhen refering to P√¢ques festivities we say ¬´ les f√™tes des P√¢ques ¬ª.\r\n\r\nIf you want to wish someone a happy easter day you only have to say ¬´ Joyeuses P√¢ques !¬ª.\r\n<h5><strong>When :</strong></h5>\r\nThe Easter day date changes from year to year as in many other countries but 