\">This movie is based on a true story. It recounts how, by the end of the 19th century, Marie Heurtin, a young blind and deaf woman learnt sign language thanks to the amazing sister Marguerite. This very moving film is the kind that makes you both smile and cry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Heurtin‚Äôs parents refused to send their daughter to an asylum (the only option the state had to offer back then). The young girl grew up like ¬´ a wild animal ¬ª and sometimes acted in a violent way.\r\nWhen her father takes her to the Larnay institute which takes care of deaf children she is labeled hopeless and would be given the boot if it wasn‚Äòt for sister Marguerite insistance to take her. This devoted nun will tame her with her love and patience and teach her how to communicate.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Those events occur in the south-western country and the general atmosphere of the movie gives a taste of what old rural France looked like 130 years ago.\r\nMarie‚Äôs story became famous in France in 1910 when Louis Arnould wrote about it in a essay named ¬´ Une √¢me en prison ¬ª ( a soul in jail). I haven‚Äôt found any translated version of that book but the original one is available for free (and legally) on the <a href=\"https://archive.org/details/UneAmeEnPrisonArnould1904%20\" target=\"_blank\">Internet archive website </a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The movie will be out on DVD on march 18th in France so it should become available abroad in the following weeks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Ce film est bas√© sur une histoire vraie. Il raconte comment, √† la fin du 19√®me si√®cle, Marie Heurtin, une jeune femme aveugle et sourde apprit la langue des signes gr√¢ce √† l‚Äôincroyable s≈ìur Marguerite. Tr√®s touchant, ce film est de ceux qui font √† la fois sourire et pleurer.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Les parents de Marie Heurtin refus√®rent d‚Äôenvoyer leur fille √† l‚Äôasile (la seule option offerte par l‚Äô√©tat √† l‚Äô√©poque). La jeune fille grandit comme ¬´ un animal sauvage ¬ª et se comportait parfois de fa√ßon violente.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Lorsque son p√®re l‚Äôemm√®ne √† l‚Äôinstitut Larnay, √©tablissement qui s‚Äôoccupe d‚Äôenfants sourds, on la classe dans les cas d√©sesp√©r√©s et elle serait renvoy√©e chez elle sans l‚Äôinsistance de s≈ìur Marguerite pour la prendre. Cette nonne d√©vou√©e va l‚Äôapprivoiser gr√¢ce √† son amour et sa patience puis lui apprendre √† communiquer.</em>\r\n<em> Ces √©v√©nements se d√©roulent dans la campagne du sud-ouest de la France et l‚Äôambiance g√©n√©rale donne un aper√ßu de ce √† quoi ressemblait la France rurale d‚Äôil y a 130 ans.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>L‚Äôhistoire de Marie devint c√©l√®bre en France en 1910 lorsque Louis Arnould √©crivit dessus dans un essai intitul√©¬´ Une √¢me en prison ¬ª. Il est disponible gratuitement (et l√©galement) <a href=\"https://archive.org/details/UneAmeEnPrisonArnould1904\" target=\"_blank\">ici</a>.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">¬†Hippocrate</span></strong></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Lc61Di-g-E4%20\" target=\"_blank\">Trailer¬† </a>\r\nIt‚Äôs a bit tricky to define that movie as it contains both elements of comedy and film noir. It explores the world of hospital and doctor‚Äôs daily dilemnas through the eyes of a rookie called Benjamin. For his first internship this idealist will have to work in the same hospital as his father and go through a rather tough initiation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Many dysfunctionnal aspects of French hospitals are exposed such as futile medical care, the omnipresence of paperwork or how profit can sometimes come before patients‚Äôwell-being‚Ä¶ Prepare for some harsh criticism and cynism as in this film, doctors are not heroes or geniuses like in Doctor house but average joes and janes who have to deal with exhausting schedules and constant pressure.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This movie was part of Cannes Festival‚Äôs selection for 2014 and was nominated for best film at the C√©sars.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can watch this movie with English subtitles on some itunes store (it‚Äôs not available in every country) or buy the DVD in French with French subtitles<a href=\"&lt;iframe%20style=&quot;width:120px;height:240px;&quot; marginwidth=&quot;0&quot; marginheight=&quot;0&quot; scrolling=&quot;no&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot; src=&quot;//ws-eu.amazon-adsystem.com/widgets/q?ServiceVersion=20070822&amp;OneJS=1&amp;Operation=GetAdHtml&amp;MarketPlace=FR&amp;source=ac&amp;ref=qf_sp_asin_til&amp;ad_type=product_link&amp;tracking_id=frenchencom-21&amp;marketplace=amazon&amp;region=FR&amp;placement=B00N43LSRE&amp;asins=B00N43LSRE&amp;linkId=PY73VMFH45LQHTNX&amp;show_border=true&amp;link_opens_in_new_window=true&quot;&gt; &lt;/iframe&gt;\" target=\"_blank\"> here</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Il est assez difficile de d√©finir ce film puisqu‚Äôil contient √† la fois des √©l√©ments comiques et d‚Äôautres qui le rapprochent du film noir. Il explore le monde hospitalier et les dilemmes quotidiens des m√©decins √† travers les yeux de Benjamin, une jeune recrue. Pour son premier internat, cet id√©aliste va devoir travailler dans le m√™me h√¥pital que son p√®re et en passer par une initiation assez dure. De nombreux dysfonctionnements du syst√®me hospitalier fran√ßais sont expos√©s, tels que l‚Äôacharnement th√©rapeutique, l‚Äôomnipr√©sence de la paperasse administrative ou encore la fa√ßon dont les b√©n√©fices passent parfois avant le bien-√™tre des patients‚Ä¶Pr√©parez-vous √† de vives critiques et du cynisme car dans ce film, les m√©decins ne sont pas des h√©ros ou des g√©nies √† la fa√ßon d‚Äôun Docteur House, mais des monsieur et madame tout le mond