nal relationship turns into a very toxic one. Sarah happens to be rather cruel and manipulative.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Respire is M√©lanie Laurent‚Äôs second movie as a director but she‚Äôs better know for her very international acting carreer : you might have seen her in Inglorious basterds, the enemy, Now you see me or Beginners. This extremely realistic movie has been shown in several French high-schools and has some pedagogical quality. Many teenagers can indeed identify with Charlie. M√©lanie Laurent herself has confessed that she has experience being bullied at school.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Dvd in French with French subtitles <a href=\"http://www.amazon.fr/gp/product/B00R1UV8B2/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1642&amp;creative=6746&amp;creativeASIN=B00R1UV8B2&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=frenchencom-21\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Respire traite d‚Äôamiti√© et d‚Äôobsession. Charlie, une ado de 17 ans timide et introvertie, est imm√©diatement fascin√©e par la nouvelle venue au lyc√©e, la charismatique et s√ªre d‚Äôelle Sarah. Elle se retrouve rapidement prise dans les filets de cette s√©ductrice et tourne le dos √† sa meilleure amie. Lentement, l‚Äôamiti√© fusionnelle se transforme en relation toxique. Sarah est en fait de nature plut√¥t cruelle et manipulatrice. Respire est le deuxi√®me film de M√©lanie Laurent en tant que r√©alisatrice mais elle est plus connue pour sa tr√®s internationale carri√®re d‚Äôactrice : vous l‚Äôavez peut-√™tre vue dans Inglorious Basterds, the enemy, Now you see me ou Beginners. Ce film tr√®s r√©aliste a √©t√© projet√© dans plusieurs lyc√©es fran√ßais pour ses qualit√©s p√©dagogiques. Beaucoup d‚Äôadolescents peuvent en effet s‚Äôidentifier √† Charlie. M√©lanie Laurent elle-m√™me a confess√© avoir fait l‚Äôexp√©rience du harc√®lement scolaire.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Thriller/suspens :</strong></h3>\r\n<h5 style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>¬†La prochaine fois je viserai le c≈ìur (next time I‚Äôll aim for the heart)</strong> </span></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><a href=\"%20https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8_fYnFVmeUw \" target=\"_blank\">Trailer</a>\r\nThis movie is definitely only for an adult audience. There aren‚Äôt any gory scenes as violence is suggested rather than explicitely shown but still the whole atmosphere is disturbing and scary !</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">This thriller, which some reviewers compared to Fincher‚Äôs <em>Zodiac</em> is adapted from the novel \'Un assassin au-dessus de tout soup√ßon\' which was inspired by macabre events that occured in France in 1978 and 1979. A killer who worked as a gendarme (rural police officer) ended up investigating his own murders.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Like in the famous Tv show<em> Dexter</em>, we‚Äôre made to see the action throught the criminal‚Äôs perspective and follow him as he goes everytime a little further in his mad frenzy¬† while trying to maintain the righteous image of the perfect cop. The comparison stops there as the audience is given no justification for Frank‚Äôs terrible acts, no reason to sympathize or understand him. The man is just crazy and can‚Äôt control himself. That‚Äôs what is the most stricking in that movie : its raw and uncompromising aspect.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">You can find the DVD (I\'m not sure it has English subtitles though) <a href=\"http://www.amazon.fr/gp/product/B00R1UV7Z4/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1642&amp;creative=6746&amp;creativeASIN=B00R1UV7Z4&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=frenchencom-21\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Ce films est d√©finitivement reserv√© √† un public adulte. Il n\'y a pas de sc√©nes gores puisque la violence est sugg√©r√©e plut√¥t qu\'explicit√©e, cependant l\'atmosph√®re est d√©rangeante et inqui√©tante. Ce thriller, que certains critiques ont compar√© √† Zodiac de David Fincher, est une adaptation du roman Un assassin au-dessus de tout soup√ßon, lui m√™me inspir√© d‚Äô√©v√©nements macabres qui eurent lieu en France entre 1978 et 1979. Un tueur faisant partie de la gendarmerie se retrouva √† enqu√™ter sur ses propres meurtres.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><em>Comme dans la c√©l√®bre s√©rie Dexter, nous assistons √† l\'action depuis la perspective du criminel et nous le suivons alors qu\'il va √† chaque fois un peu plus loin dans sa folie meurtri√®re tout en cherchant √† maintenir son image vertueuse de flic parfait. La comparaison s\'arr√™te l√† puisque le spectateur ne se voit donner aucune justification pour les actes terribles commis par Franck, aucune raison de compatir ou de le comprendre. Cet homme est juste fou et ne peut se retenir. C\'est ce qui est le plus frappant dans ce film:¬† son aspect cru et sans compromis.</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"></p>','2014 French movies you should watch (part 2) / Films fran√ßais sortis en 2014 que vous devriez regarder (2√®me partie)','','inherit','open','open','','414-revision-v1','','','2015-04-20 22:28:58','2015-04-20 20:28:58','',414,'http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/blog/2015/04/20/414-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(461,1,'2015-04-20 22:37:49','2015-04-20 20:37:49','&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/images.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-thumbnail wp-image-384\" src=\"http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/images-150x150.png\" alt=\"images\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn my last post, I recommended you listen to French as often as possible and I hope you‚Äôve followed my advice and found out how efficient it can be.\r\n\r\nFor those of you who are uninspired or simply not very familiar with French cinema, here is a list of movies you might like. As we‚Äôve just entered 2015, I thought I would pay a kind of tribute to the past year by only selecting some of 2014‚Äôs most popular French films. I haven‚Äôt seen them all but I tried to pick movies that tackle some typical aspects of French culture so you can learn a bit more about France while learning the language.\r\n\r\nAll those movies except one have been rated ¬´ suitable for all audiences ¬ª but I have to warn you that France is very liberal when it comes to depictions of sex and light violence or coarse language so some of them might still feature scenes or jokes that can be considered disturbing or offensive in other cultures. If you intend on watching those with children or teenagers you should probably check how they‚Äôve been rated in your own country.\r\n\r\nDans mon dernier article, je vous ai recommand√© d‚Äô√©couter du fran√ßais aussi souvent que possible et j‚Äôesp√®re que vous avez suivi mon conseil et constat√© √† quel point cela est efficace.\r\n\r\nPour ceux d‚Äôentre vous qui sont en manque d‚Äôinspiration ou qui ne sont tout simplement pas tr√®s cal√©s en cin√©ma fran√ßais, voici une liste de films qui pourraient vous plaire. Puisque nous venons juste d‚Äôentrer dans l‚Äôann√©e 2015, j‚Äôai pens√© √† rendre une sorte d‚Äôhommage √† l‚Äôann√©e pass√©e en s√©lectionnant uniquement des films fran√ßais parmi les plus populaires de 2014. Je ne les ai pas tous vu mais j‚Äôai essay√© de choisir des histoires qui traitent de certains aspects typiques de la culture fran√ßaise afin que vous puissiez en apprendre plus sur la France tout en apprenant la langue.\r\n\r\nTous ces films, √† l‚Äôexception d‚Äôun, ont √©t√© class√©s ¬´ tout public ¬ª mais je dois vous pr√©venir qu‚Äôen France nous avons une approche tr√®s lib√©rale quant aux repr√©sentations de sexe et de violence mod√©r√©e et √† l\'usage d\'un langage fleuri. Certaines sc√®nes ou blagues peuvent donc √™tre consid√©r√©es comme d√©rangeantes ou offensantes dans d‚Äôautres cultures. Si vous avez l‚Äôintention de visionner ces films avec des enfants ou des adolescents, vous devriez probablement v√©rifier la classification qu‚Äôils ont re√ßus dans votre pays.\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Historical/biographical movies :</strong></span></h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>- <strong>Diplomatie/ diplomacy</strong> :</h5>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qivQ-Pp1MDo\" target=\"_blank\">Trailer</a>\r\nthis very intense movie which features two of the most talented French actors- Niels arestrup and Andr√© Dussolier- recounts events that can‚Äôt be found in most of history manuals even though they played a crucial part in the unfolding of second world war in France. As the allies were about to liberate France, Hitler- in an attempt to create as much damage as possible before being defeated- ordered the destruction of Paris.\r\n\r\nMines had been planted in all the most famous and beautiful places, among them Le louvre and the Eiffel tower. On august the 25th, during long, nerve-wrecking hours, Raoul Nordling, a franco-swedish diplomat negociated with a german general called Dietrich von Choltitz.\r\n\r\nCe film tr√®s intense, servi par deux des plus talentueux acteurs fran√ßais, Niels Arestrup et Andr√© Dussolier, d√©crit des √©v√©nements qui ne figurent pas dans la plupart des manuels d‚Äôhistoire bien qu‚Äôils aient jou√© un r√¥le crucial dans la conclusion de la seconde guerre mondiale en France. Alors que les alli√©s s‚Äôappr√™taient √† lib√©rer la France, Hitler,¬† tentant de causer autant de d√©g√¢ts que possible avant d‚Äô√™tre d√©fait, ordonna la destruction de Paris.\r\n\r\nDes mines avaient √©t√© plac√©es dans tous les lieux les plus beaux et renomm√©s, parmi eux le Louvre et la Tour Eiffel. Le 25 Aout, durant de longues et angoissantes heures, Raoul Nordling, un diplomate franco-su√©dois, n√©gocia avec un g√©n√©ral allemand nomm√© Dietrich von Choltitz.\r\n\r\nDVD available on Amazon uk (with English subs) <a href=\"http://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/B00MWZSZMG/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1634&amp;creative=6738&amp;creativeASIN=B00MWZSZMG&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=frenchencom06-21\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5><strong>-¬† Yves st Laurent :</strong></h5>\r\n<strong><a href=\" https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KLKhYpPBl8o\" target=\"_blank\">Trailer</a></strong>\r\nI think most of you already have an idea who Yves st Laurent was but do you know how much he had to struggle in the very formal and strict late 50‚Äôs France to create and impose what his now one of the most prestigious haute-couture brand ? The film depicts with accuracy the art and fashion circles from 58 to 76 while focusing on the very tumultuous relationship between St Laurent and Pierre Berg√©, both his lover and business partner. I recommend this movie to every fashion lover but also to those of you who love passionate and complicated love stories.\r\n\r\nJe pense que la plupart d‚Äôentre vous a une id√©e de qui fut Yves St Laurent mais savez-vous √† quel point il a d√ª se battre, dans la¬† tr√®s stricte et formelle France de la fin des ann√©es 50, pour cr√©er et imposer ce qui est aujourd‚Äôhui devenu l‚Äôune des marques de haute-couture les plus prestigieuses ? Ce film d√©peint avec exactitude le cercle des arts et de la mode, de 58 √† 76, tout en se concentrant sur la tumultueuse relation qu‚Äôentretenaient St Laurent et Pierre Berg√©, qui fut √† la fois son amant et son partenaire en affaire.\r\n\r\nYou can buy it on <a href=\"http://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/product/B00J8FGT4E/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;camp=1634&amp;creative=6738&amp;creativeASIN=B00J8FGT4E&amp;linkCode=as2&amp;tag=frenchencom06-21\" target=\"_blank\">amazon uk¬†</a> or rent it on blinbox <a href=\"http://www.blinkbox.com/movies/yves-st-laurent-%2863419%29\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.blinkbox.com/movies/yves-st-laurent-%2863419%29</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Animation movies :</span></h4>\r\n<h5>- Jack et la m√©canique du c≈ìur (The Boy With The Cuckoo-Clock Heart)</h5>\r\nThis <a href=\"http://www.dailymotion.com/video/x22c2wf_jack-et-la-mecanique-du-coeur-the-boy-with-the-cuckoo-clock-heart-the-mechanics-of-the-heart-officia_shortfilms\" target=\"_blank\">trailer</a> is in English but most DVD offer French audio with English subtitles/ la bande-annonce est en anglais mais la plupart des DVD proposent une bande son fran√ßaise avec des sous-titres en anglais :\r\n\r\nThis animation was produced by Luc Besson (who directed subway, leon, lucy, nikita and the fifth element) and written by the leader of one France‚Äôs most popular rock band : Dionysos. This Gothic tale contains some slightly scary scenes that might not be suitable for children but should be ok for teenagers. The main character-Jack- was born on such a cold day that his heart froze and had to be replaced by a cuckoo-clock. But this a very fragile item and to keep it working Jack has to make sure to avoid strong emotions or he could die. Of course love is one of those emotions he should stay away from‚Ä¶\r\n\r\nCe film d‚Äôanimation a √©t√© produit par Luc Besson (qui a r√©alis√© Subway, Leon, Lucy, Nikita et Le cinqui√®me √©l√©ment) et √©crit par le leader d‚Äôun des groupes de rock les plus populaires de France : Dionysos. Cette fable gothique contient des sc√®nes l√©g√®rement effrayantes qui peuvent ne pas convenir √† des enfants mais qui devraient passer avec des adolescents. Le personnage principal, Jack, est n√© un jour si froid que son c≈ìur a gel√© et a d√ª √™tre remplac√© par une horloge m√©canique. Mais cet artefact est tr√®s fragile et, pour le maintenir en √©tat de marche, Jack doit s‚Äôassurer d‚Äô√©viter les √©motions fortes ou il pourrait mourir. Bien sur l‚Äôamour fait partie de ces √©motions qu‚Äôil devrait √©viter‚Ä¶\r\n\r\nAmazon.com : <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Dmovies-tv&amp;field-keywords=The