 en 1997 lors d\'un accident de voiture √† Paris.','Le royal b√©b√© est n√©: r√©cit d\'une naissance tr√®s attendue !','','inherit','open','open','','484-revision-v1','','','2015-05-08 20:31:08','2015-05-08 18:31:08','',484,'http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/blog/2015/05/08/484-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(487,1,'2015-05-11 14:00:33','2015-05-11 12:00:33','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"wp-image-500 size-full\">On May 13th the 68th edition of The Cannes International Film Festival (also known as Festival De Cannes) will start. And for many French people, this is one of the most exciting time of the year!</p>\r\n<strong> What is the festival de Cannes ? </strong>\r\n\r\nWhile the show takes place in the city of Cannes,on the French riviera,it of course displays some of the most-awaited French movies but it is mainly committed to showcasing the best of international cinema and receives submissions from many different countries.Festival De Cannes happens once a year, usually in May with a few exceptions, and is invitation only. In the 1930s the French Minister of Education opted to start the international film festival with the aid of the American and British governments and film industries.\r\n\r\nOver 15 countries participate in the film festival with the majority being located in the European Union.It didn‚Äôt take long for the festival to catch on internationally, partially due to the fact that the event is known for advocating equality amongst countries and people.The festival features for example a LGBT-related film award and was one of the first to support and display African and Latino-American movies.\r\n\r\nThe festival features competitive and non-competitive sections. The movies competing for awards are part of \"the official selection\".Among those,about 20 movies are nominated for the best film award known as the Palme d\'Or which is the most prestigious of all.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_500\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"250\"]<a href=\"http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/2015_Cannes_Film_Festival_poster.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-500 size-full\" src=\"http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/2015_Cannes_Film_Festival_poster.jpg\" alt=\" Licensed under Fair use via Wikipedia - http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:2015_Cannes_Film_Festival_poster.jpg#/media/File:2015_Cannes_Film_Festival_poster.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"341\" /></a> Cannes Film Festival poster <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2015_Cannes_Film_Festival#/media/File:2015_Cannes_Film_Festival_poster.jpg\" target=\"_blank\">wikipedia commons</a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>The 2015 edition</strong>\r\n\r\nThe 2015 Cannes Film Festival is being held from May 13th until May 24th and its official selection will consist in 48 films so a total of 73 hours of love, suspens, action and thrill.\r\n\r\nThe presidents of the main jury (the one that will vote for la Palme d\'or) will be Joel and Ethan Coen, United States\'most famous filmaking duo (Fargo,The Big Lebowski,No Country for Old Men...).The jury includes 7 other jury members, a mix of men and women from around the world.\r\n\r\n<strong>The 4 films that I would like to see the most</strong>\r\n\r\nThis year 19 movies are competing for la Palme d\'or, here are the 4 I\'m particularly excited about:\r\n\r\n<strong>The Measure of a Man</strong> (la loi du march√©) is a French film by Stephane Briz√©. It tells the story of a 51 year old man who has been unemployed for 20 months and highlights the humiliation jobseekers have to go through.As he finally starts a new job as a security officer in a supermarket and is asked to spy on his colleagues, he faces a dilemma, one that might put him back in the unemployment line...The movie raises the question of how far it is acceptable to go to secure one\'s position.It is a rather relevant question nowadays in a context of economical crisis.\r\n\r\nHere is the French trailer (sorry no English subtitles)\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qop962e4M5Y[/embed]\r\n\r\n<strong>The Lobster</strong> by Greek director Yorgos Lanthimos (but entirely in English) is a science-fiction movie with an interesting view on a futuristic society . People are not allowed to be single. If they are not able to find a partner, they are sent¬† in a hotel filled of single people to try and find a match . They have 45 days to succeed or they are transformed into the animal of their choice and sent into the wilderness. One man manages to escape the hotel though only to end up falling in love in a society in the wilderness that only accepts single people. The movie as an impressive cast with Colin Farrell, Rachel Weisz, John C. Reilly and L√©a Seydoux starring in it\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>¬†The Sea of Trees</strong> is an American movie by Gus Van Sant starring Matthew McConaughey and Naomi Watts. In Aokigahara,¬† Japan,¬† there is a mysterious forest known as The Sea of Trees. This is where locals go to contemplate life and death. Arthur, a suicidal American traveller ventures to this place¬† only to meet Takumi Nakamura who got lost in the forest. This woman will change Arthur\'s outlook on life and together they will fight to survive the forest. Van Sant has already won a Palme d\'or, in 2003, for the movie Elephant...\r\n\r\n<strong>The Valley of Love</strong> is a French movie by <span class=\"st\">Guillaume Nicloux</span>. The action takes place in the Californian Death Valley which is presented as a mysterious and maybe even supernatural¬† place. A former couple, played by Isabelle Huppert and Gerard Depardieu receive an invitation to the Death Valley. the only problem is that the¬† invitation comes from their son who has committed suicide 6 months ago.\r\n\r\nHere is the French trailer:\r\n\r\n[embed]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ca6aRd9uypw[/embed]\r\n\r\nWith so many interesting films, the Cannes Film Festival 2015 is bound to uphold the name and reputation that the past festivals have built up. Out of the films in the competition which ones would you to see?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','The Cannes International Film Festival 2015','','publish','open','open','','the-cannes-international-film-festival-2015','','','2015-05-11 20:21:32','2015-05-11 18:21:32','',0,'http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/?p=487',0,'post','',0),(488,1,'2015-05-11 12:15:21','2015-05-11 10:15:21','\r\n\r\nOn May 13th the 68th edition of The Cannes International Film Festival (also known as Festival De Cannes) will start. And to many French people, this is one of the most exciting time of the year!\r\n\r\n  While the show takes place in the city of Cannes,on the French riviera,it of course displays some of the best French movies but is also open to countries around the word and receives submissions from many different countries.   Festival De Cannes happens once a year, usually in May with a few exceptions, and is invitation only.  In the 1930s the French Minister of Education opted to start the international film festival with the aid of the American and British governments and film industries.  \r\nOver 15 countries participate in the film festival with the majority being located in the European Union.  It didn‚Äôt take long for the festival to catch on internationally, partially due to the fact that the show is known for its equality amongst countries and people.  The festival even features a LGBT-related film award.  There are a total of 21 different awards given out each year in three different categories.  The best film award is known as the Palme d\'Or award and is the most prestigious of show.\r\nThe Cannes Film Festival of 2015 is being held from May 13th until May 24th.  Over 28 films will be shown during the competition and they include a mix of longer form films and short films.  The presidents of the jury for feature film include Joel and Ethan Coen, brothers who are renowned in the film world, from the United States.  The feature film jury includes 7 other jury members, a mix of men and women from around the world.\r\nThere are three other jurries in the Cannes Film Festival of 2015.  This includes a jurry for the Cinefondation/Short Films selection, the Un Certain Regard category, and the Camera d‚Äôor selection.   All of the judges come from a variety of different backgrounds and nationalities.  Some of the backgrounds include producers, directors, actors, and songwriters.\r\nThe Cinefondation and Short Film selection is lead by Abderrahmane Sissako, a director/screenwriter/producer of Mauritanian descent who now lives in France and has traveled the globe.  Under him there are four other judges, Cecile De France (actress), Joana Hadjithomas (director), Daniel Olbrychski (Actor), and Rebecca Zlotowski (director).\r\nThe Un Certain Regard Jury is presidented by Isabella Rosellini.  Rosellini is an Italian filmmaker and actress who has also done modeling in her career.  The rest of her jury includes Haifa Al-Mansour (director), Nadine Labaki (actress/director), Panos H. Koutras (director), and Tahar Rahim (actor).\r\nThe last category, Camera d‚Äôor, is presidented by a French actress and director named Sabine Azema.  Her fellow jurors include Delphine Gleize (director), Melvil Poupaud (actor), Claude Garnier (French film industry representative), Didier Huck (French film industry representative), Yann Gonzales (French film industry representative), and Bernard Payen (french film industry representative).  This category has the second largest jury team.\r\nThe official selection for the Cannes Film Festival 2015 consists of 48 films and over 73 hours of film.  One of the films competing for the main award is The Measure of a Man a French film by Stephanie Brize.  The film is about a man who has been unemployed for 20 months at the age of 51.  It starts off by highlighting the humiliation that those who go through unemployment face.  When his job starts he faces a new dilemma, one that might put him back in the unemployment line.  How far is too far to go when you need to find work?  Brize spends time making the movie intimate and making us know the character and how he fights with society.\r\nThe Lobster is an interesting view on a future society that has a big focus.  People may not be single.  If they are single they are sent to try and find a match in a hotel full of single people.  They have 45 days to find their match or they are transformed into an animal of their choice and sent into the wilderness.  One man manages to escape the hotel though only to end up falling in love in a society in the wilderness that only accepts single people.\r\nAnother contestant is The Sea of Trees.  In Japan Aokigahara there is a forest known as The Sea of Trees.  This is where the people of Japan go to contemplate life and death.  Arthur travels around the world to this place and ventures in only to find Takumi Nakamura, a Japanese person lost in the forest.  Finding Nakamura changes Arthur‚Äôs outlook and they fight to survive the forest.\r\nThe Valley of Love turns California‚Äôs Death Valley into a place of mystery.  Parents Isabelle and Gerard are summoned by their son to Death Valley, the only problem is the invitation comes 6 months after he committed suicide.  The two launch off on a journey despite the weirdness of the invitation.\r\nWith so many interesting films, the Cannes Film Festival 2015 is bound to uphold the name and reputation that the past festivals have built up.  Out of the films in the competition which ones are you excited see?','The Cannes International Film Festival 2015','','inherit','open','open','','487-revision-v1','','','2015-05-11 12:15:21','2015-05-11 10:15:21','',487,'http://www.frenchenglishservices.com/blog/2015/05/11/487-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(489,1,'2015-05-11 12:32:36','2015-05-11 10:32:36','\r\nOn May 13th the 68th edition of The Cannes International Film Festival (also known as Festival De Cannes) will start. And to many French people, this i